    affiliation: "Aurel Vlaicu University of Arad, Romania"
repository-code: "https://github.com/vbocan/ruin_framework"
abstract: >-
  RUIN (Rigor, Utility, Integrity, Necessity) is a framework for content-level
  assessment of computer science publications along four dimensions: formalism
  proportionality, citation integrity, structural soundness, and artifact
  availability. The repository contains the framework specification, the
  ROMJIST validation dataset (415 papers, 2010–2025), and scripts to
  reproduce the published tables and figures.
keywords:
  - research evaluation
  - scientometrics
  - formalism proportionality
  - reproducibility
  - large language models
  - content-based assessment
